t on to spearhead the project he teamed up with shai sole shmuel timor and eli raban by the late s and early s the weizmann team partnered with a local israeli company aaa–advanced automated applications founded by tuvi orbach began marketing db to domestic large organizations  subsequently the company started marketing its product overseas one of the companys first overseas clients was a uk based international infrastructure firm in  in  the weizmann team established its own company to be later merged with aaa and joined by entrepreneurs ron zuckerman and shaul shani the company severed itself from the weizmann institute and was incorporated under its new name—sapiens by  sapiens had established a client base encompassing israel the united kingdom switzerland canada south africa germany and venezuela in  sapiens was registered as a public limited liability company in the netherlands antilles under the name sapiens international corporation nv in  sapiens latin american division entered the brazilian market in  shares of sapiens began trading on the nasdaq exchange the year  is considered the companys peak with  workers employed at  branches around the world and a market cap of us million during the second half of the  sapiens focused on developing a business rules technology emerge and legacy modernization products and services the company was highly successful in winning contracts for updating information systems to deal with the year  problem and to adapt systems to the changeover to the new single european currency the euro in  the companys annual revenues reached usd but declined in the following years refocusing on insurance softwareedit in  formula systems until then a minority shareholder acquired control over the then struggling company dan goldstein then chairman of the formula group assumed the role of chairman of sapiens and supervised its recovery the company decided to focus solely on developing software solution for the insurance industry in  sapiens 